div.p:
That Ariosto was honoured and respected by the first men of his age is a fact;
                    that most of the princes of Italy showed him great partiality is equally true;
                    but it is not less so that their patronage was limited to kind words. It is not
                    known that he ever received any substantial mark of their love for literature:
                    he lived and died poor. He proudly wrote on the entrance of a house built by
                    himself,
